Rudzani Matshili Ahead of the 11th annual Mams Arts music festival taking place this Saturday, a dialogue featuring celebrated entrepreneurs within the business of the arts was hosted. Actress Sophie Ndaba, Delphine Klaasen, choreographer and author Paul Modjadji, and Melba Nkosi were some of the speakers. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window.  The dialogue was held under the banner Mams Arts and Entrepreneurship 101 at Moretele Park in Mamelodi. Funding within the arts and culture sector were one of the crucial issues talked about. Local artists and aspiring entrepreneurs in attendance were advised on how to get funding for their projects and more about the entertainment industry. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window.  During the engagement, the department of arts and culture’s Dunisani Chabalala encouraged artists to always apply for funding. Lady Zamar, Ntando, Nasty C, Vusi Nova, Speedsta, Mo flava, Okmalumkoolkat, Tim Mosha,  Thando Thabethe, Amon Mokoena, Soul Kulture and Thuli P are some of the big names roped in to perform at the festival.